Mastectomy Bill in Congress

It takes 2 seconds to do this and is very important...please
take the time and do it really quick!

Breast Cancer Hospitalization Bill - Important legislation
for all women.  Please send this to everyone in your address

book. If there was ever a time when our voices and choices

should be heard, this is one of those times. If you are

receiving this it's because I think you will take the 30

seconds to go and vote on this issue and send it
on to others you know who will do the same.
 
There's a bill called the Breast Cancer Patient Protection
Act which will require insurance companies to cover a minimum

48-hour hospital stay for patients undergoing a mastectomy. It's

about eliminating the "drive-through mastectomy" where women are

forced to go home hours after surgery against the wishes of their

doctor, still groggy from anesthesia and sometimes with drainage

tubes still attached. Lifetime Television has put this bill on their

web page with a petition drive to show your support. Last year over

half the House signed on.
 
PLEASE!! Sign the petition by clicking on the web site
below. You need not give more than your name and zip code number.

http://www.lifetimetv.com/health/breast_mastectomy_pledge.html

This takes about 2 seconds. PLEASE PASS THIS ON to your
friends and family. THANKS!

many people think that i am trying to get them to change their views on things, but i am not! Sure I have an opinion about things, just like you do. But just because mine is different from yours doesn't mean that you need to dismiss it. I don't dismiss yours. And just because my views are different from yours doesn't mean that i am trying to change your opinion because it is different than mine. I am glad people have different opinions, its one of the great things about life, so many people with so many differences. I never understand it, i am having a conversation with someone about anything and then we disagree. Which people are bound to disagree eventually. And they think that b/c i am disagreeing with them means that i don't respect their opinion or their choices. Well damn it, i do respect your damn opinion. So respect my right to believe whatever i want to believe, respect my right to say whatever the hell i want to say and respect my right to disagree with what you say b/c my opinion is different than yours. It's not like i am saying "HEY, YOU STUPID SHITHEAD DON'T DO THAT!" I for one am tired of being misunderstood; i am not trying to change you or your opinion.

HAPPY EASTER!

I am currently whipping up a potato dish to bring to Shane's Grandparent's house for Easter.

Spring is my absolute favorite time of year!  Everything is warm and green.

I am hungry.  All I ate today was one sandwich.

I just heard thunder.  I wish that it would not rain.  Rain would be bad b/c I would have to bring my plants in and they need more sun.  AND I DON'T WANT IT TO RAIN ON EASTER.  I just saw lighting.  That reminds me of 'Dark of the Moon' "It's just heat lightin'" - whatever Joan's character's name was.

My neck and back hurt.  They probably hurt b/c Shane was teaching me how to head a soccer ball.  Either that or my English teacher is putting to much stress on me.

Today Shane, Brent, Gabe and I all played soccer.  Gabe asked me if I played for a league, which of course I don't b/c I have never REALLY played before.  He told me that I should play for a league.  To bad I don't think they have any female +20 leagues around here.  Perhaps I was better than I thought.  I thought I sucked.  But I think I suck at everything.  It's part of my pessimistic view of life.  

I am getting tired but I have to wait for those potato's to finish cooking.
